==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electro-magnet
<hw>E*lec`tro-mag"net</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mass,
usually of soft iron, but sometimes of some other magnetic metal, as
nickel or cobalt, rendered temporarily magnetic by being placed within a
coil of wire through which a current of electricity is passing. The
metal is generally in the form of a bar, either straight, or bent into
the shape of a horseshoe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-magnetic</ent>⟦br⟧
